<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,589,1765]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,442,1021,1046]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Known distribution.</emphasis>
Widespread throughout the Palearctic: many localities in Europe, Western 
<collectingCountry box="[1288,1365,1021,1045]" name="Russia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Russia</collectingCountry>
, Siberia, Central Asia, Western Tibet and 
<collectingCountry box="[557,621,1058,1081]" name="Japan" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Japan</collectingCountry>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Luther" box="[679,816,1057,1081]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Luther, A. (1963) Die Turbellarien Ostfenoskandiens IV. Neorhabdocoela 2. Typhloplanoida: Typhloplanidae, Solenopharyngidae und Carcharodopharyngidae. Fauna Fennica, 16, 1 - 163." type="journal article" year="1963">
Luther 
<number box="[760,816,1057,1081]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1963.0">1963</number>
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Heitkamp" box="[869,1242,1057,1081]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Heitkamp, U. &amp; Schrade-Mock, W. (1978) Speziationsprozesse bei Mesostoma lingua (Turbellaria Rhabdocoela). Acta Zoologica Fennica, 154, 47 - 57." type="journal article" year="1978">
Heitkamp &amp; Schrade-Mock 
<number box="[1186,1242,1057,1081]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1978.0">1978</number>
</bibRefCitation>
for localities and references), Western Europe (
<collectingCountry box="[496,542,1093,1117]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">UK</collectingCountry>
: West Midlands and North 
<collectingCountry box="[868,939,1093,1117]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Wales</collectingCountry>
; 
<collectingCountry box="[955,1140,1093,1117]" name="Netherlands" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">the Netherlands</collectingCountry>
: Friesland) (
<bibRefCitation author="Young" box="[1287,1432,1093,1117]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Young, J. O. (1970) British and Irish freshwater Microturbellaria: historical records, new records and a key for their identification. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, 67, 210 - 241." type="journal article" year="1970">
Young 
<number box="[1373,1432,1093,1117]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1970.1972">1970</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Young" box="[151,222,1129,1153]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Young, J. O. (1972 a) The Turbellaria of some Friesland lakes with incidental records of Gasteropoda and Hirudinea. Zoologische Bijdragen, 13, 59 - 70." type="journal article" year="1972" yearSuffix="a">1972a</bibRefCitation>
